7 Chapter 4.1. Reorganization of Certain Townships
8 Sec. 1. This chapter does not apply to a township:
9 (1) located in a county having a consolidated city; or
10 (2) that, on June 1, 2026, has begun to consolidate with
11 another:
12 (A) township under IC 36-6-1.5; or
13 (B) unit under IC 36-1.5-4; or
14 (3) located in a county in which each township located in the
15 county consolidates in accordance with subdivision (2) to
16 establish not more than one (1) township whose boundaries
17 coincide with the boundaries of the county and the
18 consolidated township would not meet the population
19 requirement described in section 6(1)(A) of this chapter.
20 Sec. 2. To the extent that other provisions in this article conflict
21 with this chapter, this chapter controls.
22 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "designated unit" means:
23 (1) a county or municipality that is named by a township in a
24 resolution under section 11 of this chapter; or
25 (2) a county to which section 12 or 21 of this chapter applies.
26 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "plan" or "plan of
27 reorganization" means a plan of reorganization approved by the
28 legislative body of a designated unit under this chapter.
29 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "reorganization" means the
30 dissolution of a township and the transfer of township property,
31 functions, powers, and services to the designated unit.
32 Sec. 6. As used in this chapter, "township" means either of the
33 following:
34 (1) A township that satisfies all of the following criteria:
35 (A) The township has a population of less than six
36 thousand seven hundred (6,700) as determined by the most
37 recent federal decennial census.
38 (B) The township does not operate a fire department. For
39 purposes of this clause, a township that is:
40 (i) a provider unit or nonprovider unit in a fire
41 protection territory; or
42 (ii) part of a fire protection district;
