1 does not operate a fire department.
2 (C) In calendar year 2024, the total value of benefits
3 provided to recipients of township assistance (as reported
4 in the township's annual statistical report under
5 IC 12-20-28-3) does not exceed two hundred percent
6 (200%) of the sum of all compensation paid to township
7 employees (as reported in the township's annual report
8 filed under IC 5-11-13-1).
9 (2) A township that satisfies all of the following criteria:
10 (A) At least eighty percent (80%) of the total area of the
11 township is located within the corporate boundaries of a
12 municipality.
13 (B) At least fifty-one percent (51%) of the township's
14 population resides within the corporate boundaries of a
15 municipality described in clause (A).
16 (C) The township does not operate a fire department. For
17 purposes of this clause, a township that is:
18 (i) a provider unit or nonprovider unit in a fire
19 protection territory; or
20 (ii) part of a fire protection district;
21 does not operate a fire department.
22 Sec. 7. As used in this chapter, "township office" refers to any
23 of the following:
24 (1) The office of township trustee elected as provided in
25 IC 36-6-4-2.
26 (2) The office of township assessor elected as provided in
27 IC 36-6-5-1 (if the office exists).
28 (3) The office of a member of the township board elected as
29 provided in IC 36-6-6-2.
30 Sec. 8. As used in this chapter, "township services" means the
31 following:
32 (1) Township assistance under IC 12-20 and IC 12-30-4.
33 (2) Provision of insulin to the poor under IC 12-20-16.
34 (3) Fire protection services under IC 36-8.
35 (4) Fence viewing under IC 32-26.
36 (5) Provision and maintenance of cemeteries under IC 23-14.
37 (6) Provision and maintenance of township parks and
38 community centers under IC 36-10.
39 (7) Destruction of detrimental plants, noxious weeds, and rank
40 vegetation under IC 15-16-8.
41 (8) Any other services required by statute to be provided by
42 a township.
