1 Sec. 9. (a) On January 1, 2028, each township is dissolved. All of
2 the following occur:
3 (1) The term of office of an individual who holds a township
4 office ends on December 31, 2027. An election for a township
5 office shall not be held in 2028 or thereafter.
6 (2) The:
7 (A) powers and duties of the office of township trustee are
8 transferred to the executive of the designated unit;
9 (B) legislative powers and duties of the office of township
10 board members are transferred to the legislative body of
11 the designated unit;
12 (C) fiscal powers and duties of the office of township board
13 members are transferred to the fiscal body of the
14 designated unit; and
15 (D) powers and duties of the township assessor (if the office
16 exists) are transferred to the county assessor.
17 (3) The boundaries of the dissolved township remain as the
18 boundaries of the service area within which the designated
19 unit provides township services.
20 (4) If a township participates in a fire protection territory or
21 fire protection district, the fire protection territory or fire
22 protection district is unaffected by the reorganization and the
23 area within the boundaries of the dissolved township remain
24 a part of the fire protection territory or fire protection district
25 after reorganization. The designated unit succeeds the
26 township in the township's role as:
27 (A) provider unit or nonprovider unit in the fire protection
28 territory; or
29 (B) participant in the fire protection district;
30 for the area within the boundaries of the dissolved township.
31 (5) The balance in the general fund of the township shall be
32 transferred to the general fund of the designated unit.
33 (6) The balance in the township assistance fund of a township
34 shall be transferred to a township assistance fund established
35 by the designated unit.
36 (7) The balance of any other fund of the township shall be
37 transferred to the fund of the designated unit that most
38 closely corresponds to the fund of the township.
39 (8) Subject to section 26 of this chapter, the property and
40 liabilities of the township become the property and liabilities
41 of the designated unit.
42 (b) IC 36-1-8-5 does not apply to a balance referred to in
