3 Sec. 14. (a) A joint board shall consist of the following:
4 (1) Two (2) members of the township board of each township
5 participating in the reorganization, selected by the members
6 of the township board.
7 (2) Four (4) members of the legislative body of the designated
8 municipality or of the fiscal body of the designated county,
9 whichever is applicable, selected by the members of the body.
10 (3) The township trustee of the township, the fiscal officer of
11 the designated municipality or county, and other members of
12 the bodies under subdivisions (1) and (2) shall serve as
13 advisory, nonvoting members.
14 (b) Four (4) voting members constitute a quorum. Official
15 action may only be taken by affirmative vote of at least a majority
16 of members present at the meeting.
17 (c) The members of a joint board serve without compensation.
18 The members are entitled to reimbursement from the reorganizing
19 township and designated units for the necessary expenses incurred
20 in the performance of their duties.
21 (d) A joint board is subject to IC 5-14-1.5 and IC 5-14-3.
22 (e) The joint board shall prepare a reorganization plan not later
23 than December 1, 2026, for transferring the powers, duties, and
24 property of the township consistent with this chapter. The joint
25 board shall send the plan to the legislative body of the designated
26 unit for adoption.
27 (f) The legislative body of the designated unit may adopt the
28 plan as drafted or modify the plan before adoption.
29 Sec. 15. Elimination of a township office does not invalidate:
30 (1) any resolutions, fees, schedules, or other actions adopted
31 or taken by the township trustee or township assessor (if the
32 office exists) before January 1, 2028; or
33 (2) any appointments made by the township trustee or
34 township assessor (if the office exists) before January 1, 2028.
35 Sec. 16. In 2027, the fiscal body of the designated unit shall, in
36 the manner provided by IC 6-1.1-17, adopt a budget, tax levies, and
37 tax rates that are sufficient for the designated unit to provide
38 township services within the boundaries of the dissolved township.
39 Sec. 17. (a) The plan of reorganization governs the actions,
40 duties, and powers of the designated unit and the township that are
41 not specified by law.
42 (b) The plan of reorganization must be consistent with this
